-- Five facts about P&G's Robert McDonald
-- 
-- Wed Jun 10, 2009 9:19am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/06/10/us-procter-factbox-sidebar-idUSTRE55936920090610

 

 (Reuters) - Procter & Gamble Co ( PG.N ) named Robert McDonald as its new chief executive on Wednesday, replacing A.G. Lafley, who has held the post for nine years. 

 Here are five facts about McDonald. * Robert McDonald was born June 20, 1953 in Gary, Indiana, and grew up in Chicago. * He graduated from the U.S. Military Academy at West Point in 1975 and got his MBA from the University of Utah in 1978. * McDonald served as a U.S. Army captain from 1975-1980, primarily in the 82nd Airborne Division. * He joined Cincinnati-based P&G on June 4, 1980. * McDonald has held several positions at P&G in the United States, Canada, Japan, Korea, the Philippines and Belgium. He was named vice chairman of global operations in 2004 and became chief operating officer in 2007. (Source: P&G; Reporting by Jessica Wohl; Editing by Lisa Von Ahn)